# Workspace Filesystem Protocol

## MCP tool

The `claude-workspace` MCP tool is scoped to:
- `/Users/sean.sands/claude-workspace` (symlink → Drive/Claude Workspace)
- `/Users/sean.sands/projects`

Available to all models in Cursor; per `01-agent-controller.mdc`, only Claude writes.

## Claude — allowed without confirmation

- Read any workspace file to answer context questions
- Write artifacts to `04-artifacts/active/` (naming convention required)
- Update `06-context/project-context.md`, `session-log.md`, `artifact-registry.md`
- Update skills in `02-skills/` when explicitly requested
- Run `08-tools/compile-cursor-rules.py` to sync compiled outputs

## Claude — requires user confirmation

- Modifying `00-frameworks/` or `03-preferences/user-preferences.md`
- Modifying any file in `00-bootstrap/`
- Deleting or archiving any skill directory
- Writing to `.cursor/rules/` outside of the compile script

## Obsidian conventions (always preserve)

- `[[wikilinks]]` for internal links — graph depends on them
- YAML frontmatter on metadata-bearing notes
- Tags: lowercase + hyphenated
- Tasks: `- [ ]` open, `- [x]` done
- Artifact names: `context_descriptor_vN.N_YYYY-MM-DD.ext`
- Never delete — move to `_archive/`

## Compile script

Syncs context files → `AGENTS.md`. Run after changes to `06-context/` or `03-preferences/`.

```bash
cd "/Users/sean.sands/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-hello@snds.design/My Drive/Claude Workspace"
python3 08-tools/compile-cursor-rules.py
# watch mode:
python3 08-tools/compile-cursor-rules.py --watch
```
